        public Config getOwnConfig(ConfigKeyPath configKey)
        Obtains the configuration properties directly associated with a given config keys. These will not include any properties/values which can be obtained from the ancestors or imported config keys..

        This implementation simply delegate the functionality to the internal ConfigStore/version

      • getResolvedConfig

        public Config getResolvedConfig(ConfigKeyPath configKey)
        Obtains a Config object with all implicit and explicit imports resolved, i.e. specified using the Config.withFallback(com.typesafe.config.ConfigMergeable) API..

        This implementation simply delegate the functionality to the internal ConfigStore/version if the internal ConfigStore is ConfigStoreWithResolution, otherwise based on ConfigStoreTopologyInspector 1. find out all the imports recursively 2. resolved the config on the fly

        Specified by:
        getResolvedConfig in interface ConfigStoreValueInspector
        Parameters:
        configKey - the path of the configuration key to be resolved
        Returns:
        the Config object associated with the specified config key with all direct and indirect imports resolved.
